I was getting the same behavior.  I worked around it by using a class like the following, although I think a better fix would be to interrupt the connection upon stop as the workaround requires 30s in the worst case.

```
public class MyProcessor extends StringDelimitedProcessor {
   private long lastMessage = System.currentTimeMillis();

   public MyProcessor(BlockingQueue<String> queue) {
      super(queue);
   }

   @Override
   public boolean process() throws IOException, InterruptedException {
      String msg = processNextMessage();
      while (msg == null) {
         if (System.currentTimeMillis() - lastMessage > 5000) {
            lastMessage = System.currentTimeMillis();
            return true;
         }
         msg = processNextMessage();
      }
      lastMessage = System.currentTimeMillis();
      return queue.offer(msg, offerTimeoutMillis, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);
   }
}
```

